The paper discusses the visualization of statistical data, which is a topic that falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of data aggregators and the integration of different data sources suggest a focus on database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of coordinated visualizations, which is a common technique in graph drawing and information visualization (cs.GR). The integration of user visualizations and the use of mouse over effects suggest a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and interactive systems (cs.SI).
